other group. Average survival was 538 days in the lung cancer group and 668 days 
in the other group. The procedure was well tolerated, with only one 
postoperative complication, which was a minor wound infection.
CONCLUSION: For patients suffering from advanced malignancy, medialization 
thyroplasty is a safe procedure and an excellent modality for voice palliation.

