variations may make this procedure more complicated. We describe two cases of 
patients with situs viscerum inversus and acute myocardial infarction who 
underwent successful transradial percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI). We 
will show that coronary angioplasty with stent application via the radial 
approach in patients with DC is feasible and effective also in emergency and 
urgent care.

